50785 - Analyze capture-mark-recapture data using mrmr

Roland Knapp

This notebook analyzes capture-mark-recapture data using the mrmr package. The code creates the required survey, capture, and translocation data frames from saved CSV files (created by xxxxx_createdata_mrmr.Rmd), checks the datasets, fits the model, evaluates potential non-convergence of the MCMC algorithm, and visualizes model results.

Install latest versions of cmdstanr, cmdstan, and mrmr packages

Run only if updated versions were released since previous install

# install cmdstanr and cmdstan
install.packages("cmdstanr", repos = c("https://mc-stan.org/r-packages/", getOption("repos")))
cmdstanr::install_cmdstan()

# install mrmr
remotes::install_github("SNARL1/mrmr")

Check datasets

data_50785 <- clean_data(captures = captures, surveys = surveys, translocations = translocations)
Joining, by = c("primary_period", "secondary_period", "survey_date", "year", "is_overwinter")Joining, by = "survey_date"Joining, by = "survey_date"Joining, by = c("pit_tag_id", "y")Joining, by = "survey_date"Joining, by = c("primary_period", "secondary_period")Joining, by = c("primary_period", "secondary_period", "y")Joining, by = c("primary_period", "secondary_period", "y")Joining, by = c("primary_period", "secondary_idx")Warning: All captured individuals appear to have been introduced (that is, they are in the translocation data). For computational reasons, the model will not include a natural recruitment component. If this is consistent with your understanding, proceed without concern. But if there are naturally recruited individuals that have been captured, please check the data.

Fit model

Code assumes that there are 8 physical cores available. Update parallel_chains and threads_per_chain as necessary based on actual number of cores. Add “control = list(adapt_delta = 0.99)” or similar if divergent transitions occur.

model_50785 <- fit_model(
                    data = data_50785, 
                    chains = 4, 
                    parallel_chains = 4, 
                    cpp_options = list(stan_threads = TRUE),
                    threads_per_chain = 2)
